35void PopulateRtpWithCodecSpecifics(const CodecSpecificInfo& info,
36 absl::optional<int> spatial_index,
37 RTPVideoHeader* rtp) {
38 rtp->codec = info.codecType;
39 rtp->is_last_frame_in_picture = info.end_of_picture;
40 switch (info.codecType) {
41 case kVideoCodecVP8: {
42 auto& vp8_header = rtp->video_type_header.emplace<RTPVideoHeaderVP8>();
43 vp8_header.InitRTPVideoHeaderVP8();
44 vp8_header.nonReference = info.codecSpecific.VP8.nonReference;
45 vp8_header.temporalIdx = info.codecSpecific.VP8.temporalIdx;
46 vp8_header.layerSync = info.codecSpecific.VP8.layerSync;
47 vp8_header.keyIdx = info.codecSpecific.VP8.keyIdx;
48 rtp->simulcastIdx = spatial_index.value_or(0);
49 return;
50 }
51 case kVideoCodecVP9: {
52 auto& vp9_header = rtp->video_type_header.emplace<RTPVideoHeaderVP9>();
53 vp9_header.InitRTPVideoHeaderVP9();
54 vp9_header.inter_pic_predicted =
55 info.codecSpecific.VP9.inter_pic_predicted;
56 vp9_header.flexible_mode = info.codecSpecific.VP9.flexible_mode;
57 vp9_header.ss_data_available = info.codecSpecific.VP9.ss_data_available;
58 vp9_header.non_ref_for_inter_layer_pred =
59 info.codecSpecific.VP9.non_ref_for_inter_layer_pred;
60 vp9_header.temporal_idx = info.codecSpecific.VP9.temporal_idx;
61 vp9_header.temporal_up_switch = info.codecSpecific.VP9.temporal_up_switch;
62 vp9_header.inter_layer_predicted =
63 info.codecSpecific.VP9.inter_layer_predicted;
64 vp9_header.gof_idx = info.codecSpecific.VP9.gof_idx;
65 vp9_header.num_spatial_layers = info.codecSpecific.VP9.num_spatial_layers;
66 vp9_header.first_active_layer = info.codecSpecific.VP9.first_active_layer;
67 if (vp9_header.num_spatial_layers > 1) {
68 vp9_header.spatial_idx = spatial_index.value_or(kNoSpatialIdx);
69 } else {
70 vp9_header.spatial_idx = kNoSpatialIdx;
71 }
72 if (info.codecSpecific.VP9.ss_data_available) {
73 vp9_header.spatial_layer_resolution_present =
74 info.codecSpecific.VP9.spatial_layer_resolution_present;
75 if (info.codecSpecific.VP9.spatial_layer_resolution_present) {
76 for (size_t i = 0; i < info.codecSpecific.VP9.num_spatial_layers;
77 ++i) {
78 vp9_header.width[i] = info.codecSpecific.VP9.width[i];
79 vp9_header.height[i] = info.codecSpecific.VP9.height[i];
80 }
81 }
82 vp9_header.gof.CopyGofInfoVP9(info.codecSpecific.VP9.gof);
83 }
84
85 vp9_header.num_ref_pics = info.codecSpecific.VP9.num_ref_pics;
86 for (int i = 0; i < info.codecSpecific.VP9.num_ref_pics; ++i) {
87 vp9_header.pid_diff[i] = info.codecSpecific.VP9.p_diff[i];
88 }
89 vp9_header.end_of_picture = info.end_of_picture;
90 return;
91 }
92 case kVideoCodecH264: {
93 auto& h264_header = rtp->video_type_header.emplace<RTPVideoHeaderH264>();
94 h264_header.packetization_mode =
95 info.codecSpecific.H264.packetization_mode;
96 rtp->simulcastIdx = spatial_index.value_or(0);
97 return;
98 }
99#ifndef DISABLE_H265
100 case kVideoCodecH265: {
101 auto& h265_header = rtp->video_type_header.emplace<RTPVideoHeaderH265>();
102 h265_header.packetization_mode =
103 info.codecSpecific.H265.packetization_mode;
104 rtp->simulcastIdx = spatial_index.value_or(0);
105 return;
106 }
107#endif
108 case kVideoCodecMultiplex:
109 case kVideoCodecGeneric:
110 rtp->codec = kVideoCodecGeneric;
111 rtp->simulcastIdx = spatial_index.value_or(0);
112 return;
113 default:
114 return;
115 }
116}
117
118void SetVideoTiming(const EncodedImage& image, VideoSendTiming* timing) {
119 if (image.timing_.flags == VideoSendTiming::TimingFrameFlags::kInvalid ||
120 image.timing_.flags == VideoSendTiming::TimingFrameFlags::kNotTriggered) {
121 timing->flags = VideoSendTiming::TimingFrameFlags::kInvalid;
122 return;
123 }
124
125 timing->encode_start_delta_ms = VideoSendTiming::GetDeltaCappedMs(
126 image.capture_time_ms_, image.timing_.encode_start_ms);
127 timing->encode_finish_delta_ms = VideoSendTiming::GetDeltaCappedMs(
128 image.capture_time_ms_, image.timing_.encode_finish_ms);
129 timing->packetization_finish_delta_ms = 0;
130 timing->pacer_exit_delta_ms = 0;
131 timing->network_timestamp_delta_ms = 0;
132 timing->network2_timestamp_delta_ms = 0;
133 timing->flags = image.timing_.flags;
134}

137RtpPayloadParams::RtpPayloadParams(const uint32_t ssrc,
138 const RtpPayloadState* state,
139 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials)
140 : ssrc_(ssrc),
141 generic_picture_id_experiment_(
142 absl::StartsWith(trials.Lookup("WebRTC-GenericPictureId"),
143 "Enabled")),
144 simulate_generic_vp9_(
145 absl::StartsWith(trials.Lookup("WebRTC-Vp9DependencyDescriptor"),
146 "Enabled")) {
147 for (auto& spatial_layer : last_shared_frame_id_)
148 spatial_layer.fill(-1);
149
150 buffer_id_to_frame_id_.fill(-1);
151
152 Random random(rtc::TimeMicros());
153 state_.picture_id =
154 state ? state->picture_id : (random.Rand<int16_t>() & 0x7FFF);
155 state_.tl0_pic_idx = state ? state->tl0_pic_idx : (random.Rand<uint8_t>());
156}
157
158RtpPayloadParams::RtpPayloadParams(const RtpPayloadParams& other) = default;
159
160RtpPayloadParams::~RtpPayloadParams() {}

162RTPVideoHeader RtpPayloadParams::GetRtpVideoHeader(
163 const EncodedImage& image,
164 const CodecSpecificInfo* codec_specific_info,
165 int64_t shared_frame_id) {
166 RTPVideoHeader rtp_video_header;
167 if (codec_specific_info) {
168 PopulateRtpWithCodecSpecifics(*codec_specific_info, image.SpatialIndex(),
169 &rtp_video_header);
170 }
171 rtp_video_header.frame_type = image._frameType;
172 rtp_video_header.rotation = image.rotation_;
173 rtp_video_header.content_type = image.content_type_;
174 rtp_video_header.playout_delay = image.playout_delay_;
175 rtp_video_header.width = image._encodedWidth;
176 rtp_video_header.height = image._encodedHeight;
177 rtp_video_header.color_space = image.ColorSpace()
178 ? absl::make_optional(*image.ColorSpace())
179 : absl::nullopt;
180 rtp_video_header.video_frame_tracking_id = image.VideoFrameTrackingId();
181 SetVideoTiming(image, &rtp_video_header.video_timing);
182
183 const bool is_keyframe = image._frameType == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey;
184 const bool first_frame_in_picture =
185 (codec_specific_info && codec_specific_info->codecType == kVideoCodecVP9)
186 ? codec_specific_info->codecSpecific.VP9.first_frame_in_picture
187 : true;
188
189 SetCodecSpecific(&rtp_video_header, first_frame_in_picture);
190
191 SetGeneric(codec_specific_info, shared_frame_id, is_keyframe,
192 &rtp_video_header);
193
194 return rtp_video_header;
195}
196
197uint32_t RtpPayloadParams::ssrc() const {
198 return ssrc_;

201RtpPayloadState RtpPayloadParams::state() const {
202 return state_;

205void RtpPayloadParams::SetCodecSpecific(RTPVideoHeader* rtp_video_header,
206 bool first_frame_in_picture) {
207 // Always set picture id. Set tl0_pic_idx iff temporal index is set.
208 if (first_frame_in_picture) {
209 state_.picture_id = (static_cast<uint16_t>(state_.picture_id) + 1) & 0x7FFF;
210 }
211 if (rtp_video_header->codec == kVideoCodecVP8) {
212 auto& vp8_header =
213 absl::get<RTPVideoHeaderVP8>(rtp_video_header->video_type_header);
214 vp8_header.pictureId = state_.picture_id;
215
216 if (vp8_header.temporalIdx != kNoTemporalIdx) {
217 if (vp8_header.temporalIdx == 0) {
218 ++state_.tl0_pic_idx;
219 }
220 vp8_header.tl0PicIdx = state_.tl0_pic_idx;
221 }
222 }
223 if (rtp_video_header->codec == kVideoCodecVP9) {
224 auto& vp9_header =
225 absl::get<RTPVideoHeaderVP9>(rtp_video_header->video_type_header);
226 vp9_header.picture_id = state_.picture_id;
227
228 // Note that in the case that we have no temporal layers but we do have
229 // spatial layers, packets will carry layering info with a temporal_idx of
230 // zero, and we then have to set and increment tl0_pic_idx.
231 if (vp9_header.temporal_idx != kNoTemporalIdx ||
232 vp9_header.spatial_idx != kNoSpatialIdx) {
233 if (first_frame_in_picture &&
234 (vp9_header.temporal_idx == 0 ||
235 vp9_header.temporal_idx == kNoTemporalIdx)) {
236 ++state_.tl0_pic_idx;
237 }
238 vp9_header.tl0_pic_idx = state_.tl0_pic_idx;
239 }
240 }
241 if (generic_picture_id_experiment_ &&
242 rtp_video_header->codec == kVideoCodecGeneric) {
243 rtp_video_header->video_type_header.emplace<RTPVideoHeaderLegacyGeneric>()
244 .picture_id = state_.picture_id;
245 }
246}
247
248RTPVideoHeader::GenericDescriptorInfo
249RtpPayloadParams::GenericDescriptorFromFrameInfo(
250 const GenericFrameInfo& frame_info,
251 int64_t frame_id) {
252 RTPVideoHeader::GenericDescriptorInfo generic;
253 generic.frame_id = frame_id;
254 generic.dependencies = dependencies_calculator_.FromBuffersUsage(
255 frame_id, frame_info.encoder_buffers);
256 generic.chain_diffs =
257 chains_calculator_.From(frame_id, frame_info.part_of_chain);
258 generic.spatial_index = frame_info.spatial_id;
259 generic.temporal_index = frame_info.temporal_id;
260 generic.decode_target_indications = frame_info.decode_target_indications;
261 generic.active_decode_targets = frame_info.active_decode_targets;
262 return generic;
263}
264
265void RtpPayloadParams::SetGeneric(const CodecSpecificInfo* codec_specific_info,
266 int64_t frame_id,
267 bool is_keyframe,
268 RTPVideoHeader* rtp_video_header) {
269 if (codec_specific_info && codec_specific_info->generic_frame_info &&
270 !codec_specific_info->generic_frame_info->encoder_buffers.empty()) {
271 if (is_keyframe) {
272 // Key frame resets all chains it is in.
273 chains_calculator_.Reset(
274 codec_specific_info->generic_frame_info->part_of_chain);
275 }
276 rtp_video_header->generic = GenericDescriptorFromFrameInfo(
277 *codec_specific_info->generic_frame_info, frame_id);
278 return;
279 }
280
281 switch (rtp_video_header->codec) {
282 case VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecGeneric:
283 GenericToGeneric(frame_id, is_keyframe, rtp_video_header);
284 return;
285 case VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecVP8:
286 if (codec_specific_info) {
287 Vp8ToGeneric(codec_specific_info->codecSpecific.VP8, frame_id,
288 is_keyframe, rtp_video_header);
289 }
290 return;
291 case VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecVP9:
292 if (simulate_generic_vp9_ && codec_specific_info != nullptr) {
293 Vp9ToGeneric(codec_specific_info->codecSpecific.VP9, frame_id,
294 *rtp_video_header);
295 }
296 return;
297 case VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecAV1:
298 // TODO(philipel): Implement AV1 to generic descriptor.
299 return;
300 case VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecH264:
301 if (codec_specific_info) {
302 H264ToGeneric(codec_specific_info->codecSpecific.H264, frame_id,
303 is_keyframe, rtp_video_header);
304 }
305 return;
306#ifndef DISABLE_H265
307 case VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecH265:
308 // FIXME: Implement H265 to generic descriptor.
309 return;
310#endif
311 case VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecMultiplex:
312 return;
313 }
314 RTC_NOTREACHED() << "Unsupported codec.";
315}
316
317void RtpPayloadParams::GenericToGeneric(int64_t shared_frame_id,
318 bool is_keyframe,
319 RTPVideoHeader* rtp_video_header) {
320 RTPVideoHeader::GenericDescriptorInfo& generic =
321 rtp_video_header->generic.emplace();
322
323 generic.frame_id = shared_frame_id;
324
325 if (is_keyframe) {
326 last_shared_frame_id_[0].fill(-1);
327 } else {
328 int64_t frame_id = last_shared_frame_id_[0][0];
329 RTC_DCHECK_NE(frame_id, -1);
330 RTC_DCHECK_LT(frame_id, shared_frame_id);
331 generic.dependencies.push_back(frame_id);
332 }
333
334 last_shared_frame_id_[0][0] = shared_frame_id;
335}
336
337void RtpPayloadParams::H264ToGeneric(const CodecSpecificInfoH264& h264_info,
338 int64_t shared_frame_id,
339 bool is_keyframe,
340 RTPVideoHeader* rtp_video_header) {
341 const int temporal_index =
342 h264_info.temporal_idx != kNoTemporalIdx ? h264_info.temporal_idx : 0;
343
344 if (temporal_index >= RtpGenericFrameDescriptor::kMaxTemporalLayers) {
345 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Temporal and/or spatial index is too high to be "
346 "used with generic frame descriptor.";
347 return;
348 }
349
350 RTPVideoHeader::GenericDescriptorInfo& generic =
351 rtp_video_header->generic.emplace();
352
353 generic.frame_id = shared_frame_id;
354 generic.temporal_index = temporal_index;
355
356 if (is_keyframe) {
357 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(temporal_index, 0);
358 last_shared_frame_id_[/*spatial index*/ 0].fill(-1);
359 last_shared_frame_id_[/*spatial index*/ 0][temporal_index] =
360 shared_frame_id;
361 return;
362 }
363
364 if (h264_info.base_layer_sync) {
365 int64_t tl0_frame_id = last_shared_frame_id_[/*spatial index*/ 0][0];
366
367 for (int i = 1; i < RtpGenericFrameDescriptor::kMaxTemporalLayers; ++i) {
368 if (last_shared_frame_id_[/*spatial index*/ 0][i] < tl0_frame_id) {
369 last_shared_frame_id_[/*spatial index*/ 0][i] = -1;
370 }
371 }
372
373 RTC_DCHECK_GE(tl0_frame_id, 0);
374 RTC_DCHECK_LT(tl0_frame_id, shared_frame_id);
375 generic.dependencies.push_back(tl0_frame_id);
376 } else {
377 for (int i = 0; i <= temporal_index; ++i) {
378 int64_t frame_id = last_shared_frame_id_[/*spatial index*/ 0][i];
379
380 if (frame_id != -1) {
381 RTC_DCHECK_LT(frame_id, shared_frame_id);
382 generic.dependencies.push_back(frame_id);
383 }
384 }
385 }
386
387 last_shared_frame_id_[/*spatial_index*/ 0][temporal_index] = shared_frame_id;
388}
389
390void RtpPayloadParams::Vp8ToGeneric(const CodecSpecificInfoVP8& vp8_info,
391 int64_t shared_frame_id,
392 bool is_keyframe,
393 RTPVideoHeader* rtp_video_header) {
394 const auto& vp8_header =
395 absl::get<RTPVideoHeaderVP8>(rtp_video_header->video_type_header);
396 const int spatial_index = 0;
397 const int temporal_index =
398 vp8_header.temporalIdx != kNoTemporalIdx ? vp8_header.temporalIdx : 0;
399
400 if (temporal_index >= RtpGenericFrameDescriptor::kMaxTemporalLayers ||
401 spatial_index >= RtpGenericFrameDescriptor::kMaxSpatialLayers) {
402 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Temporal and/or spatial index is too high to be "
403 "used with generic frame descriptor.";
404 return;
405 }
406
407 RTPVideoHeader::GenericDescriptorInfo& generic =
408 rtp_video_header->generic.emplace();
409
410 generic.frame_id = shared_frame_id;
411 generic.spatial_index = spatial_index;
412 generic.temporal_index = temporal_index;
413
414 if (vp8_info.useExplicitDependencies) {
415 SetDependenciesVp8New(vp8_info, shared_frame_id, is_keyframe,
416 vp8_header.layerSync, &generic);
417 } else {
418 SetDependenciesVp8Deprecated(vp8_info, shared_frame_id, is_keyframe,
419 spatial_index, temporal_index,
420 vp8_header.layerSync, &generic);
421 }
422}
423
424FrameDependencyStructure RtpPayloadParams::MinimalisticVp9Structure(
425 const CodecSpecificInfoVP9& vp9) {
426 const int num_spatial_layers = vp9.num_spatial_layers;
427 const int num_temporal_layers = kMaxTemporalStreams;
428 FrameDependencyStructure structure;
429 structure.num_decode_targets = num_spatial_layers * num_temporal_layers;
430 structure.num_chains = num_spatial_layers;
431 structure.templates.reserve(num_spatial_layers * num_temporal_layers);
432 for (int sid = 0; sid < num_spatial_layers; ++sid) {
433 for (int tid = 0; tid < num_temporal_layers; ++tid) {
434 FrameDependencyTemplate a_template;
435 a_template.spatial_id = sid;
436 a_template.temporal_id = tid;
437 for (int s = 0; s < num_spatial_layers; ++s) {
438 for (int t = 0; t < num_temporal_layers; ++t) {
439 // Prefer kSwitch for indication frame is part of the decode target
440 // because RtpPayloadParams::Vp9ToGeneric uses that indication more
441 // often that kRequired, increasing chance custom dti need not to
442 // use more bits in dependency descriptor on the wire.
443 a_template.decode_target_indications.push_back(
444 sid <= s && tid <= t ? DecodeTargetIndication::kSwitch
445 : DecodeTargetIndication::kNotPresent);
446 }
447 }
448 a_template.frame_diffs.push_back(tid == 0 ? num_spatial_layers *
449 num_temporal_layers
450 : num_spatial_layers);
451 a_template.chain_diffs.assign(structure.num_chains, 1);
452 structure.templates.push_back(a_template);
453
454 structure.decode_target_protected_by_chain.push_back(sid);
455 }
456 if (vp9.ss_data_available && vp9.spatial_layer_resolution_present) {
457 structure.resolutions.emplace_back(vp9.width[sid], vp9.height[sid]);
458 }
459 }
460 return structure;
461}
462
463void RtpPayloadParams::Vp9ToGeneric(const CodecSpecificInfoVP9& vp9_info,
464 int64_t shared_frame_id,
465 RTPVideoHeader& rtp_video_header) {
466 const auto& vp9_header =
467 absl::get<RTPVideoHeaderVP9>(rtp_video_header.video_type_header);
468 const int num_spatial_layers = vp9_header.num_spatial_layers;
469 const int num_temporal_layers = kMaxTemporalStreams;
470
471 int spatial_index =
472 vp9_header.spatial_idx != kNoSpatialIdx ? vp9_header.spatial_idx : 0;
473 int temporal_index =
474 vp9_header.temporal_idx != kNoTemporalIdx ? vp9_header.temporal_idx : 0;
475
476 if (spatial_index >= num_spatial_layers ||
477 temporal_index >= num_temporal_layers ||
478 num_spatial_layers > RtpGenericFrameDescriptor::kMaxSpatialLayers) {
479 // Prefer to generate no generic layering than an inconsistent one.
480 return;
481 }
482
483 RTPVideoHeader::GenericDescriptorInfo& result =
484 rtp_video_header.generic.emplace();
485
486 result.frame_id = shared_frame_id;
487 result.spatial_index = spatial_index;
488 result.temporal_index = temporal_index;
489
490 result.decode_target_indications.reserve(num_spatial_layers *
491 num_temporal_layers);
492 for (int sid = 0; sid < num_spatial_layers; ++sid) {
493 for (int tid = 0; tid < num_temporal_layers; ++tid) {
494 DecodeTargetIndication dti;
495 if (sid < spatial_index || tid < temporal_index) {
496 dti = DecodeTargetIndication::kNotPresent;
497 } else if (spatial_index != sid &&
498 vp9_header.non_ref_for_inter_layer_pred) {
499 dti = DecodeTargetIndication::kNotPresent;
500 } else if (sid == spatial_index && tid == temporal_index) {
501 // Assume that if frame is decodable, all of its own layer is decodable.
502 dti = DecodeTargetIndication::kSwitch;
503 } else if (sid == spatial_index && vp9_header.temporal_up_switch) {
504 dti = DecodeTargetIndication::kSwitch;
505 } else if (!vp9_header.inter_pic_predicted) {
506 // Key frame or spatial upswitch
507 dti = DecodeTargetIndication::kSwitch;
508 } else {
509 // Make no other assumptions. That should be safe, though suboptimal.
510 // To provide more accurate dti, encoder wrapper should fill in
511 // CodecSpecificInfo::generic_frame_info
512 dti = DecodeTargetIndication::kRequired;
513 }
514 result.decode_target_indications.push_back(dti);
515 }
516 }
517
518 // Calculate frame dependencies.
519 static constexpr int kPictureDiffLimit = 128;
520 if (last_vp9_frame_id_.empty()) {
521 // Create the array only if it is ever used.
522 last_vp9_frame_id_.resize(kPictureDiffLimit);
523 }
524 if (vp9_header.inter_layer_predicted && spatial_index > 0) {
525 result.dependencies.push_back(
526 last_vp9_frame_id_[vp9_header.picture_id % kPictureDiffLimit]
527 [spatial_index - 1]);
528 }
529 if (vp9_header.inter_pic_predicted) {
530 for (size_t i = 0; i < vp9_header.num_ref_pics; ++i) {
531 // picture_id is 15 bit number that wraps around. Though undeflow may
532 // produce picture that exceeds 2^15, it is ok because in this
533 // code block only last 7 bits of the picture_id are used.
534 uint16_t depend_on = vp9_header.picture_id - vp9_header.pid_diff[i];
535 result.dependencies.push_back(
536 last_vp9_frame_id_[depend_on % kPictureDiffLimit][spatial_index]);
537 }
538 }
539 last_vp9_frame_id_[vp9_header.picture_id % kPictureDiffLimit][spatial_index] =
540 shared_frame_id;
541
542 // Calculate chains, asuming chain includes all frames with temporal_id = 0
543 if (!vp9_header.inter_pic_predicted && !vp9_header.inter_layer_predicted) {
544 // Assume frames without dependencies also reset chains.
545 for (int sid = spatial_index; sid < num_spatial_layers; ++sid) {
546 chain_last_frame_id_[sid] = -1;
547 }
548 }
549 result.chain_diffs.resize(num_spatial_layers);
550 for (int sid = 0; sid < num_spatial_layers; ++sid) {
551 if (chain_last_frame_id_[sid] == -1) {
552 result.chain_diffs[sid] = 0;
553 continue;
554 }
555 result.chain_diffs[sid] = shared_frame_id - chain_last_frame_id_[sid];
556 }
557
558 if (temporal_index == 0) {
559 chain_last_frame_id_[spatial_index] = shared_frame_id;
560 if (!vp9_header.non_ref_for_inter_layer_pred) {
561 for (int sid = spatial_index + 1; sid < num_spatial_layers; ++sid) {
562 chain_last_frame_id_[sid] = shared_frame_id;
563 }
564 }
565 }
566}

568void RtpPayloadParams::SetDependenciesVp8Deprecated(
569 const CodecSpecificInfoVP8& vp8_info,
570 int64_t shared_frame_id,
571 bool is_keyframe,
572 int spatial_index,
573 int temporal_index,
574 bool layer_sync,
575 RTPVideoHeader::GenericDescriptorInfo* generic) {
576 RTC_DCHECK(!vp8_info.useExplicitDependencies);
577 RTC_DCHECK(!new_version_used_.has_value() || !new_version_used_.value());
578 new_version_used_ = false;
579
580 if (is_keyframe) {
581 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(temporal_index, 0);
582 last_shared_frame_id_[spatial_index].fill(-1);
583 last_shared_frame_id_[spatial_index][temporal_index] = shared_frame_id;
584 return;
585 }
586
587 if (layer_sync) {
588 int64_t tl0_frame_id = last_shared_frame_id_[spatial_index][0];
589
590 for (int i = 1; i < RtpGenericFrameDescriptor::kMaxTemporalLayers; ++i) {
591 if (last_shared_frame_id_[spatial_index][i] < tl0_frame_id) {
592 last_shared_frame_id_[spatial_index][i] = -1;
593 }
594 }
595
596 RTC_DCHECK_GE(tl0_frame_id, 0);
597 RTC_DCHECK_LT(tl0_frame_id, shared_frame_id);
598 generic->dependencies.push_back(tl0_frame_id);
599 } else {
600 for (int i = 0; i <= temporal_index; ++i) {
601 int64_t frame_id = last_shared_frame_id_[spatial_index][i];
602
603 if (frame_id != -1) {
604 RTC_DCHECK_LT(frame_id, shared_frame_id);
605 generic->dependencies.push_back(frame_id);
606 }
607 }
608 }
609
610 last_shared_frame_id_[spatial_index][temporal_index] = shared_frame_id;
611}
612
613void RtpPayloadParams::SetDependenciesVp8New(
614 const CodecSpecificInfoVP8& vp8_info,
615 int64_t shared_frame_id,
616 bool is_keyframe,
617 bool layer_sync,
618 RTPVideoHeader::GenericDescriptorInfo* generic) {
619 RTC_DCHECK(vp8_info.useExplicitDependencies);
620 RTC_DCHECK(!new_version_used_.has_value() || new_version_used_.value());
621 new_version_used_ = true;
622
623 if (is_keyframe) {
624 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(vp8_info.referencedBuffersCount, 0u);
625 buffer_id_to_frame_id_.fill(shared_frame_id);
626 return;
627 }
628
629 constexpr size_t kBuffersCountVp8 = CodecSpecificInfoVP8::kBuffersCount;
630
631 RTC_DCHECK_GT(vp8_info.referencedBuffersCount, 0u);
632 RTC_DCHECK_LE(vp8_info.referencedBuffersCount,
633 arraysize(vp8_info.referencedBuffers));
634
635 for (size_t i = 0; i < vp8_info.referencedBuffersCount; ++i) {
636 const size_t referenced_buffer = vp8_info.referencedBuffers[i];
637 RTC_DCHECK_LT(referenced_buffer, kBuffersCountVp8);
638 RTC_DCHECK_LT(referenced_buffer, buffer_id_to_frame_id_.size());
639
640 const int64_t dependency_frame_id =
641 buffer_id_to_frame_id_[referenced_buffer];
642 RTC_DCHECK_GE(dependency_frame_id, 0);
643 RTC_DCHECK_LT(dependency_frame_id, shared_frame_id);
644
645 const bool is_new_dependency =
646 std::find(generic->dependencies.begin(), generic->dependencies.end(),
647 dependency_frame_id) == generic->dependencies.end();
648 if (is_new_dependency) {
649 generic->dependencies.push_back(dependency_frame_id);
650 }
651 }
652
653 RTC_DCHECK_LE(vp8_info.updatedBuffersCount, kBuffersCountVp8);
654 for (size_t i = 0; i < vp8_info.updatedBuffersCount; ++i) {
655 const size_t updated_id = vp8_info.updatedBuffers[i];
656 buffer_id_to_frame_id_[updated_id] = shared_frame_id;
657 }
658
659 RTC_DCHECK_LE(buffer_id_to_frame_id_.size(), kBuffersCountVp8);
660}
